PN,46107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1773421882
OL,3,CFirst Minister speaks to Prime
OL,4,CMinister over leaked devolution memo
OL,6,FIn a copy of what appeared to be the
OL,7,Fletter, seen by the Press Association,
OL,8,Fthe Prime Minister said the UK
OL,9,FGovernment needed to demonstrate it
OL,10,Fhad a hand in people's lives in areas
OL,11,Fof Britain with devolved governments,
OL,12,Fespecially ahead of May's elections.
OL,14,FPlaid's Llyr Gruffydd asked whether
OL,15,Fthe First Minister agreed with her
OL,16,Fparty colleague Mick Antoniw, who had
OL,17,Fsuggested the Wales Office should be
OL,18,Fscrapped.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1773421882
OL,3,CFirst Minister speaks to Prime
OL,4,CMinister over leaked devolution memo
OL,6,F"I think there's a role for the Wales
OL,7,FOffice. I think there's a lot of areas
OL,8,Fof reserved responsibility," Baroness
OL,9,FMorgan replied.
OL,11,F"I think having a Wales voice at the
OL,12,FCabinet table should be of help to us.
OL,14,F"What I don't want to see is the Wales
OL,15,FOffice being used as the voice of the
OL,16,FUK Government in Wales."
OL,18,FSpeaking afterwards, Mr Gruffydd said:
OL,19,F"The First Minister must have been
OL,20,Freading a different memo to everyone
OL,21,Felse.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@\O]sD@AOUvD@AOUxD@XO]{D@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1773421882
OL,3,CFirst Minister speaks to Prime
OL,4,CMinister over leaked devolution memo
OL,6,F"There's no doubt that the Prime
OL,7,FMinister's memo gave clear instruction
OL,8,Ffor his Cabinet members to override
OL,9,FWelsh Government and other devolved
OL,10,Fgovernments to spend directly, even in
OL,11,Ftimes of disagreement.
OL,13,F"This is yet another example of this
OL,14,FLabour Welsh Government putting party
OL,15,Fbefore country."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUwD@PO]
